Tic-Tac-Toe

-Use case description

-The 1st player chooses X and the other player chooses O. First played places the cross on board and 2nd player places O. One player wins and game ends else draw happens.

-Triggers
First player puts cross on board.

-Actors
Player1
Player2
Board (3X3)
Board Game

-Predictions
-2 players avaiable 
-Board is available



-Goals
Game ends in Draw
Game ends in One player winning

-Further Extensions

-Extend it for NXN

-Exec steps:

-1st player puts X
-2nd player's turn to put O
-Repeat upto the point the board is filled , Tell who wins.